items.title: Tough stuff: Spider silk enhanced with graphene-based materials
items.summary: Natural spider silk has excellent mechanical properties. Researchers have now found a way to boost the strength of spider’s silk using graphene-based materials, paving the way for a novel class of high-performance bionic composites.

items.title: Magnetic fields to alleviate anxiety
items.summary: It is possible to unlearn fears. And this works even better when a specific region of the brain has previously been stimulated magnetically.

items.title: Delayed weaning reduces behavioural problems in cats
items.summary: Early weaning increases aggression and stereotypic behavior in cats. Based on the study, the recommended weaning age of 12 weeks should be raised by at least two weeks. Delaying weaning is an easy and cost-efficient way of improving the quality of life of cats.

items.title: Black Sea water temperatures may buck global trend
items.summary: Scientists have successfully simulated the Black Sea’s long term currents, salt water content and temperature for the first time.
